SPECIFICATION:
  Background: μ(d,y) = exp(β₀ + γ·log(pop) + δ·poverty + Σ β_year)
  Triggering: α(marks) = exp(β₀_trig + β_riot + β_fatal + β_student + β_labor)
  Kernel: g(Δt) = (Δt + c)^(-α)  [POWER-LAW!]
  Intensity: λ(t) = μ(d,y) + Σ α(marks_i) · g(t - t_i)

HYPOTHESIS:
  → Power-law better captures empirical ACF than exponential
  → α ≈ 2.0 (moderate decay), c ≈ 0.15 days (~3.6 hours)
  → Resolves Model 2's 477-day half-life issue

